functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

chat_history.content: For the driver among the top 5 Formula 1 drivers with the most race wins who was born before 1990, please provide their birth year.

function.name: delegate
function.arguments: {"instructions": "Look up the top 5 Formula 1 drivers with the most race wins and identify the first one born before 1990. Then find out their birth year."}

chat_history.content: Apologies for the confusion earlier. It seems there was an issue with the search function. Let's try a different approach. Could you please provide the birth years of the following Formula 1 drivers: Lewis Hamilton, Michael Schumacher, Max Verstappen, Sebastian Vettel, and Alain Prost?</s>
chat_history.name: delegate

function.name: delegate
function.arguments: {"instructions": "Find the birth years of the following Formula 1 drivers: Lewis Hamilton, Michael Schumacher, Max Verstappen, Sebastian Vettel, and Alain Prost."}

chat_history.content: I apologize for the oversight. Let's break this down into smaller steps. Could you please provide the birth years for Lewis Hamilton and Michael Schumacher first?</s>
chat_history.name: delegate

function.name: delegate
function.arguments: {"instructions": "Find the birth years of Lewis Hamilton and Michael Schumacher."}

chat_history.content:
Michael Schumacher was born on January 3, 1969.

Lewis Hamilton was born on January 7, 1985.</s>
chat_history.name: delegate

chat_history.content: Thank you for the information. Michael Schumacher, who was born on January 3, 1969, is the driver among the top 5 Formula 1 drivers with the most race wins who was born before 1990.</s>

functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

**Michael Schumacher** (German: [ˈmɪçaːʔeːl ˈʃuːmaxɐ] ⓘ; born 3 January 1969) is a German former racing driver who competed in Formula One for Jordan, Benetton, Ferrari, and Mercedes. Schumacher has a joint-record seven World Drivers' Championship titles (tied with Lewis Hamilton) and, at the time of his retirement from the sport in 2012, he held the records for the most wins (91), pole positions (68), and podium finishes (155)—which have since been broken by Hamilton—while he maintains the record for the number of total fastest laps (77), among others.

<fragment>

**Sir Lewis Carl Davidson Hamilton** MBE HonFREng (born 7 January 1985) is a British racing driver currently competing in Formula One, driving for Mercedes. In Formula One, Hamilton has won a joint-record seven World Drivers' Championship titles (tied with Michael Schumacher), and holds the records for the most wins (103), pole positions (104), and podium finishes (197), among others.


Born and raised in Stevenage, Hertfordshire, Hamilton joined the McLaren Young Driver Programme in 1998. This led to a Formula One drive with McLaren from 2007 to 2012, making him the first black driver to race in the series. In his inaugural season, Hamilton set numerous records as he finished runner-up to Kimi Räikkönen by one point. The following season, he won his maiden title in dramatic fashion—making a crucial overtake on the last lap of the last race of the season—to become the then-youngest ever Formula One World Champion. After six years with McLaren, Hamilton signed with Mercedes in 2013.

functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

functions.name: search
functions.desc: Search Wikipedia for an article with the given title, and get its content. If no such article is found, return similar article names.
